# Pull Request Template Requirements

When creating a pull request (using `gh pr create`), you MUST strictly follow the PR template at `.github/pull_request_template.md`. Every section must be filled in — do NOT leave any section blank.

## Required Sections

1. **Type of Change**: Check exactly one box that matches the change type (Bug Fix, New Feature, etc.)
2. **Related Issues**: Link related issue numbers (e.g., `Closes #123`)
3. **Summary of Changes**: Write 2-5 sentences describing what changed and why
4. **Checklist**: Check all items that apply; `make pre-commit` must always be checked
5. **Impact**: Check applicable boxes; if none apply, leave all unchecked but add "No breaking changes" under Additional Notes
6. **Additional Notes**: Add testing steps, deployment notes, or "N/A" if nothing extra

## Example

```markdown
## Type of Change
- [ ] New Feature
- [x] Bug Fix
- [ ] Documentation

## Related Issues
Closes #2036

## Summary of Changes
Fixed anonymous access being denied when no PublicAccessBlock configuration exists.
`get_public_access_block_config` returning `ConfigNotFound` was incorrectly treated
as an access denial. Now it is handled as "no restrictions" per AWS S3 semantics.

## Checklist
- [x] I have read and followed the CONTRIBUTING.md guidelines
- [x] Passed `make pre-commit`
- [x] Added/updated necessary tests
- [ ] Documentation updated (if needed)
- [ ] CI/CD passed (if applicable)

## Impact
- [ ] Breaking change (compatibility)
- [ ] Requires doc/config/deployment update

## Additional Notes
Workaround for users who cannot upgrade: run `put-public-access-block` with all
options set to false on affected buckets.
```
